Summary of Today's Learning
1. Setting Up WordPress Locally
XAMPP Installation Path: installed XAMPP in E:\JCU\Bridge\Content Management Systems\Xampp
WordPress Directory: extracted WordPress to E:\JCU\Bridge\Content Management Systems\Xampp\Xampp\htdocs\wordpress
Accessing WordPress: visit  http://localhost/wordpress

2. Fixing "Error Establishing a Database Connection"
Ensure MySQL is running (Start it in the XAMPP Control Panel).
Check database credentials in wp-config.php:
define('DB_NAME', 'wordpress_db'); //database name
define('DB_USER', 'root');         // Default username is root
define('DB_PASSWORD', '');         // Default password is empty
define('DB_HOST', 'localhost');    // Default hostname is localhost
If MySQL uses port 3307, update wp-config.php:
define('DB_HOST', 'localhost:3307');
Verify the database exists in phpMyAdmin.

